# Digit and Odd/Even Classification Project

This project uses the MNIST dataset to perform digit classification and odd/even classification.

## Description

The project is divided into two main tasks:

1. Digit Classification: Classify handwritten digits from the MNIST dataset.
2. Odd/Even Classification: Determine whether a given digit is odd or even.

The project is implemented in Python, using various machine learning libraries.

## Installation

To set up and run the project, follow these steps:

1. Clone the repository or download the files to your local machine.
2. Navigate to the project directory (e.g., `cd ~/Desktop/task5`).
3. Install the necessary libraries and packages using the command `pip install -r requirements.txt`.

## Usage

To run the project, execute the Jupyter notebook in the project directory.

